subclause.text:
the application describes with reasonable particularity the matter to be seized and, to the extent
			 reasonable under the circumstances, identifies the location where the
			 matter is to be seized;

clause.text:
in exceptional circumstances that render an injunction inequitable, that conditions future use of
			 the trade secret upon payment of a reasonable royalty for no longer than
			 the period of time for which such use could have been prohibited;

in lieu of damages measured by any other methods, the damages caused by the misappropriation
			 measured by imposition of liability for a reasonable royalty for the
			 misappropriator’s unauthorized disclosure or use of the trade secret;
